Definition {#definition .unnumbered}
==========

Let $f\colon X\to Y$ be a function from a set $X$ to a set $Y$. If $A$
is a subset of $X$, then the *restriction of $f$ to $A$* is the function
$$\begin{aligned}
f|_A\colon A&\to& Y \\
      x&\mapsto& f(x).\end{aligned}$$ Some authors write
$f\upharpoonright A$ instead of $f|_A$.

Properties {#properties .unnumbered}
==========

If $A\subseteq X$, and $B\subseteq Y$, then $$\begin{aligned}
 (f|_A)^{-1}(B)&=&A\cap f^{-1}(B).\end{aligned}$$
